author: Doug Knoop
title: Celebration of Mary Tyler Moore’s television career
text:
‘Mary Tyler Moore: A Celebration’ An hourlong look at the actress that starred in two of the best television sitcoms in the 1960s-70s (“The Dick Van Dyke Show” and “The Mary Tyler Moore Show”). The special features interviews with Moore, Betty White, Ed Asner, Valerie Harper, Cloris Leachman, Carl Reiner, Dick Van Dyke and Oprah Winfrey. 8 p.m. Tuesday, Oct. 13, on KCTS.
Doug Knoop: dknoop@seattletimes.com or on Twitter @dougknoop

“The Flash,” 8 p.m. (The CW): A mysterious man has a warning about an evil speedster intent on destroying The Flash; a determined officer wants to join Joe’s meta-human task force.
“The Grinder,” 8:30 p.m. (Fox): Stewart dismisses Dean’s claims that Claire is sharing secrets with a rival firm; Deb and Claire strike up a gossipy friendship, making Stewart question Claire’s trustworthiness.
“Marvel’s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.,” 9 p.m. (ABC): Mack, Daisy and Coulson race against time to keep Lincoln safe; Hunter will do whatever it takes to get revenge.
“Chicago Fire,” 10 p.m. (NBC): During an undercover operation, Casey lands in dangerous territory; Dawson’s suspicions are confirmed; a new candidate (Steven R. McQueen) makes an unusual first impression; a protest hinders firefighters who are trying to battle a blaze.
“Limitless,” 10 p.m. (CBS): Sen. Edward Morra’s representative asks Brian to take the FBI’s secret files on NZT; Harris makes a discovery that leaves her feeling conflicted.
